# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to only predict the sign of the product of all the element in the array.
1. If we found 0 return 0 because anything one multipled to 0 will be 0 only.
2. Initalize a counter and count the total negative element present in the array.
3. If negative count is mutliple of 2 then the product output will be positive number so retrun 1.
4. If negative count is not a mutliple of 2 then the product output will be negative number so retrun 0.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int arraySign(int[] nums) {
        int countMinus = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < nums.length ; i ++){
            if(nums[i] == 0){
                return 0; // return 0 if we found a 0 in the array
            }
            if(nums[i] < 0){
                countMinus++; //increment the count wehn we found a negative number
            }
        }
        //check if countMinus is multiple of 2 then return 1 else return -1
        return countMinus % 2 == 0 ? 1 : -1;
    }
}
```
