# Intuition
First Approach-01:
In this we create a `signFunc` as stated in the question 
Then We simply do the product of all elements in vector and then pass it to the `signFunc` 
Main trick to this Question is **Modulo operator**
As the product will exceed the int or long long Range so to overcome that we have to use a number to limit the product and to limit a number so that it dont cross a specific range we use Modulo operator 

The task is to determine which number we can take as the upper limit
So for that we will go for 1e9+7 (i.e. 1000000007) as it is the highest prime number close to the range of int data type.
*P.S. you can google it to know more about it *

Second Approach-02:(**Easy and Brainer way**)
In this method we are counting the no. of negative elements and if we found a zero we will return the 0

if we dont then we simply check the count of negative number,
if count is multiple of two then the resultant product will always be a positive number 
else it will be a negative number



