# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We will maintain a counter to calculate the negative values in the array.
If the counter got the even value after traversing the whole array, it means the product of all array elements will be positive.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Traverse the array, 
If any element in the array appears to be 0, simply return 0;
If we encounter any negative value then we will increase our negativeCount by 1;

We dont have to deal with positive values as positive*positive is always positive.

In the last we will check if negativeCount is even or not, if its even, then product will be positive, else it will be negative.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int arraySign(int[] nums) {
        //counter to keep track of negative values
        int negativeCount = 0;
        //Traversing the loop
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++) {
            //If any array element is 0, product will be zero
            if(nums[i] == 0) {
                return 0;
            }
            //If negative number, then increase the negativeCount by 1
            if(nums[i] < 0) {
                negativeCount++;
            }
        }
        //If negativeCount is even, product will be positive, hence return 1
        if(negativeCount%2 == 0) {
            return 1;
        } else {    //negativeCount is odd, product will be negative
            return -1; 
        }
    }
}
```

